HEADWORD: Ragout
<hw>Ra*gout"</hw> <pr>(r⟦adot⟧*g⟦oomac⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>rago⟦ucir⟧t</ets>, fr. <ets>rago⟦ucir⟧ter</ets> to restore one's
appetite, fr. L. pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>ad</ets> to +
<ets>gustare</ets> to taste, <ets>gustus</ets> taste. See <er>Gust</er>
relish.]</ety> <def>A dish made of pieces of meat, stewed, and highly
seasoned; <as>as, a <ex>ragout</ex> of mutton</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

